# ── Orbit environment ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. Everything here is optional EXCEPT an LLM endpoint
# (set it here or in the app's Settings). Values here override security-config.json.
#
# IMPORTANT for Docker: docker compose `env_file` does NOT strip inline "# ..."
# comments the way dotenv does — keep comments on their OWN lines (as below), or a
# value like DASHBOARD_ORIGIN will silently include the comment text.
# Also: PORT/HOST are ignored inside the container (the entrypoint forces backend
# 127.0.0.1:6800 + dashboard 0.0.0.0:6801); they only apply to bare-metal runs.

# ── Core ──
# backend port (bare-metal only; Docker forces it)
PORT=6800
# bind host; set 0.0.0.0 (or an IP) ONLY if nginx runs on a DIFFERENT host — then
# ORBIT_SUPERADMIN_KEY is mandatory and firewall this port to the proxy (bare-metal only)
# HOST=127.0.0.1
# dashboard origin (CORS + OIDC redirect base)
DASHBOARD_ORIGIN=http://localhost:6801
# public origin harnesses/agents reach this Orbit at, e.g. https://orbit.example.com
# Pins the pairing/harness URLs (forces wss:// in the connection descriptor) so a
# proxy that mis-sets X-Forwarded-Proto can't break the harness WebSocket. Set this
# whenever Orbit is behind TLS you don't fully control (chained proxies, CF Tunnel).
# ORBIT_PUBLIC_ORIGIN=https://orbit.example.com
# where per-session workspaces live (default ~/.orbit)
# ORBIT_HOME=~/.orbit

# ── Access control (RBAC + multi-tenancy) ──
# ORBIT_SUPERADMIN_KEY is the superadmin BEARER credential for programmatic API
# access (send as Authorization: Bearer / x-api-key). If set, the API + WS require
# a valid credential (this key, a tenant API key, an SSO session, or a device
# token). Unset = local/household dev-mode: loopback-only, every caller is
# treated as superadmin, no login. Tenant-scoped API keys are created from the
# Admin console, not here. (ORBIT_API_KEY / AEGIS_API_KEY are still read as
# fallbacks so pre-existing .env files keep working.)
# ORBIT_SUPERADMIN_KEY=
#
# Browser sign-in uses a local ACCOUNT (username + password), NOT the key above.
# The account is seeded at boot from these vars (or, if no password is set, a
# random one is generated and printed to the server log on first boot). You can
# change the password later from the app.
# ORBIT_SUPERADMIN_USERNAME=admin
# ORBIT_SUPERADMIN_PASSWORD=

# ── Enterprise SSO (OIDC — OPTIONAL; toggle on from Admin › SSO once set) ──
# Works with any OIDC IdP: Azure AD / Entra, Okta, Google, Auth0, Keycloak, …
# Register a "web" (confidential) app and set its redirect URI to
#   <DASHBOARD_ORIGIN>/api/auth/sso/callback   (shown in Admin › SSO).
# OIDC_ISSUER_URL=https://login.microsoftonline.com/<tenant-id>/v2.0
# OIDC_CLIENT_ID=
# OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OIDC_REDIRECT_URI=                         # optional; default <DASHBOARD_ORIGIN>/api/auth/sso/callback
# OIDC_SCOPES=openid email profile           # optional
# OIDC_ADMIN_EMAILS=alice@corp.com,bob@corp.com  # optional: these sign in as tenant-admins
# OIDC_ALLOWED_DOMAINS=corp.com              # optional: restrict sign-in to these email domains

# ── LLM (REQUIRED — any OpenAI-compatible endpoint: OpenAI, Groq, OpenRouter,
#    Together, Ollama, vLLM, a LiteLLM proxy, … Orbit only speaks /v1 HTTP) ──
# This is the UPSTREAM the app talks to. Local, app-spawned agents (pi) never see
# it directly — they go through the app's internal LLM gateway, which holds this
# key server-side. Only the app needs to reach this URL.
# Neutral LLM_* names are primary. The historical LITELLM_* / OPENAI_* names are
# still read as fallbacks, so existing .env files keep working unchanged.
# NOTE: leave LLM_BASE_URL blank if you have no endpoint yet — the UI will then
# prompt you to add one. A stale non-empty value is worse than empty: it makes
# the app dial a dead address instead of falling back cleanly.
LLM_BASE_URL=
LLM_API_KEY=
LLM_MODEL=
# Fallback aliases (optional; used only if the LLM_* above are unset):
# LITELLM_BASE_URL=   LITELLM_KEY=   LITELLM_MODEL=
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=    OPENAI_API_KEY=   OPENAI_MODEL=

# Internal LLM gateway key (OPTIONAL). Local agents authenticate to the app's own
# /llm/v1 gateway with this app-local key; the real upstream key above stays in
# the app. Auto-generated per boot if unset — pin it only if you want it stable.
# ORBIT_GATEWAY_KEY=

# ── Harness binaries (auto-discovered if installed on PATH; override if needed) ──
# PI_CLI_PATH=/path/to/pi
# PI_NODE_PATH=/path/to/node
# OPENCODE_PATH=opencode                    # for the OpenCode harness (npm i -g opencode-ai)

# ── Browser (Lightpanda; auto-started via Docker on boot) ──
# LIGHTPANDA_WS=ws://127.0.0.1:9222

# ── Execution sandbox (containment for agent shell/tools) ──
# Where a session runs when the request/profile doesn't specify one:
#   host (default) | container (ephemeral Docker, filesystem-isolated) | remote
# ORBIT_DEFAULT_SANDBOX=host
# Container sandbox image — ships BOTH python + node so generated scripts run
# without an install step. Fetched on first use (--pull missing) then cached.
# ORBIT_SANDBOX_IMAGE=nikolaik/python-nodejs:python3.12-nodejs22-slim
# ORBIT_SANDBOX_PULL=missing               # missing (default) | never (air-gapped: pre-load the image) | always
# Tighten the container sandbox (defaults preserve today's behavior exactly):
# ORBIT_SANDBOX_PI_CONFIG_RO=1              # mount host ~/.pi read-only (protect pi auth)
# ORBIT_SANDBOX_NETWORK=bridge             # non-host isolates net; publishes host.docker.internal

# ── Run API (headless task submission → result contract) ──
# Sandbox for /api/run when the request/profile doesn't set one. Runs default to
# `container` (network-on smoke tests), downgrading to host if Docker is absent.
# ORBIT_RUN_SANDBOX=container
# Layered timeouts so a run ALWAYS reaches a terminal status:
# ORBIT_RUN_IDLE_MS=180000                  # abort if the harness emits no events for this long (hang)
# ORBIT_RUN_MAX_MS=1200000                  # absolute backstop per run (~20 min)
# Built-in ask_questions tool: how long a run/turn parks at `awaiting_input`
# waiting for the user/parent-app to answer before returning a "no answer" sentinel.
# The idle watchdog is suspended while waiting; the backstop above still applies.
# ORBIT_ASK_TIMEOUT_MS=600000               # 10 min

# ── External build+test facility (orbit-build end_build handoff) ──
# When set, end_build submits the run's artifacts to this facility's /grade
# endpoint and merges the verdict into the contract's `build` block. Unset = the
# handoff is inert (end_build returns a `skipped` verdict). The facility itself is
# a SEPARATE service (see plans/external-testing-facility.md).
# ORBIT_TESTER_URL=https://tester.internal
# ORBIT_TESTER_KEY=...                      # bearer token sent to the facility

# ── Secrets / tokens encryption-at-rest ──
# Key for encrypting stored secrets + connection tokens (crypto-store.js). If
# unset, a random key is generated once and persisted to a gitignored file. Pin
# it (any strong string) to keep encrypted data readable across hosts/rebuilds.
# ORBIT_SECRET=

# ── Text-to-Speech (OPTIONAL — the voice UI only appears when these are set) ──
# LOCAL_TTS_URL=http://127.0.0.1:6767
# LOCAL_TTS_KEY=
# LOCAL_TTS_MODEL=pocket-tts

# ── Web search backends (OPTIONAL — for pi's native web_search; Orbit ships a keyless search MCP too) ──
# EXA_API_KEY=
# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ── Telegram (OPTIONAL — bot token is added encrypted via the Connectors UI, not here) ──
# TELEGRAM_DISABLE=1                        # set to disable the Telegram poller entirely

# ── Database ──
# Two interchangeable backends, chosen at boot (see agent-backend/db/adapter.js):
#   • sqlite   — Node's built-in node:sqlite. Zero-config default for bare-metal /
#                local / single-box. Persisted at ORBIT_DB_PATH (or agent-backend/orbit.db).
#   • postgres — set DATABASE_URL. The default for the Docker compose stack (which
#                ships a `postgres` service) and the right choice for networked /
#                multi-writer / future API-exposure deployments.
# Resolution: ORBIT_DB_DRIVER wins if set; else DATABASE_URL present → postgres; else sqlite.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://orbit:orbit@localhost:5432/orbit
# ORBIT_DB_DRIVER=sqlite                     # force a driver regardless of DATABASE_URL
# ORBIT_DB_PATH=/data/orbit.db               # sqlite file location (Docker mounts a volume here)
# POSTGRES_USER / POSTGRES_PASSWORD / POSTGRES_DB — compose's postgres service creds (match DATABASE_URL)
#
# Migrate an existing SQLite DB into Postgres (one-time, idempotent):
#   DATABASE_URL=postgres://orbit:orbit@localhost:5432/orbit \
#   ORBIT_SQLITE_PATH=agent-backend/orbit.db node agent-backend/scripts/migrate-sqlite-to-pg.js
